    "description": "This does a few different things:\r\n\r\n* refactors `YTInstInfoCmd` and `YTVersionCmd` so they use less copy/pasted `print()` logic.\r\n* removes a duplicate version of `get_yt_version()` from `yt.utilities.command_line`, instead relying on the version in `yt.funcs`\r\n* More gracefully catches an `hglib.error.ServerError` inside `get_hg_version` to avoid triggering a traceback.\r\n* Makes the output of `yt update`, `yt update --all`, and `yt version` a bit nicer for conda-based installs. It now detects whether the python is from Continuum (and thus likely managed by conda) and suggests doing `conda update yt`.",
